  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f088a693aa11f39b0f3cccad2141d3",
        "content": [
          "* When the user uploads a file show top 1000 rows\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When users ask to add data to a file always show all the columns and add the additional data at the end of the file\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When users asks to add additional file, always add from the vg_customer_snapshot_panel ----ask Tom\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* If a user has uploaded multiple files, and he asks for data for users in his file, by default take the file that was last uploaded.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When answering a request about an uploaded file- always mention the relevant file name on top of your answer.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When the user ask for numbers per day/week/month/year (for example- how many registrations/FTDs)- always ask for the time frame.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When adding columns, do not filter empty values. ----ask Tom\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* First Action = First Open Position = First open pos = first open trade\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When a users asks for dates columns (e.g registration, FTD), by default give the values in date format, unless he asks explicitly for DateTime (date+hour).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* EOD = end of day (yesterday eod).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* ACC = accumulative all time.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* There are 3 verification levels 1->2->3\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* There are multiple asset types: Stocks, Crypto, FX/Comm/Ind, Copy.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When a user asks for Equity/PnL/IsActive for Stocks or Crypto- you need to ask if he wants Real or CFD positions or both without split. If for both- for Equity and PnL you can just sum the numbers, for Active (boolean)- you need to take the max out of 1 or 0. \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When a user asks for data per day/month etc- by default order the result by the date column.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* A club member are all users that are not bronze"
        ]
      }
    ]
